T|Kahn|4|The pre-mortem must address these scenarios explicitly:
T|Kahn|5|
T|Kahn|6|Launch Blind: SS26 goes live w/ zero pre-cg baselines. Assume 30–40% first-month ROAS underperformance. What's the contingency budget tolerance? At what ROAS does mc pull spend?
T|Kahn|7|Pipeline Activates at T-3 Days: One snapshot, not two. Is that sufficient for a directional launch decision? ro's stance: yes — one data point is infinitely better than zero, and the alternative (delay + miss the SS26 window) carries its own cost.
T|Kahn|8|Pipeline Activates at T+7 Days (post-launch): First week of spend runs blind. Retroactive op begins in week 2. Is this acceptable? ro's stance: only if Phase 1 tst budget is capped at $1,000 total — waste is contained to a known quantity.
T|Kahn|9|Pipeline Never Activates: SS26 runs entirely on benchmarks, not data. ro's Phase 1-3 framework above is the operating plan. mc must decide: is this acceptable or does SS26 get paused?
