T|Cros|0|The pivot changes everything and nothing. ro will no longer write "HOLD — no data" briefs. Today's brief provides the framework for operating w/o data. But the framework's first sentence in every phase is "only activates IF data is flowing." The bottleneck hasn't moved — a 2-minute .env.local edit still unlocks ka, ro, nt, and fx simultaneously. The pivot just means ro stops waiting and starts planning contingencies.
T|Cros|1|
T|Cros|2|The War Room Overhaul completion is the most important signal in today's brief. Engineering capacity exists. The "reprioritization" excuse is gone. The single thing standing btw yv and a functioning mk an pipeline is a sb key that hasn't been copied into a config file. ka's June 12 brief is right: this is no longer a prioritization question — it's an execution question.
T|Cros|3|
T|Cros|4|Monday, June 16 is the real deadline. Not SS26 launch. Not the pre-mortem. Monday is when data must start flowing to have 2 pre-cg snapshots before launch. If .env.local isn't filled by Monday, ro's SS26 recommendation shifts from "tst budget w/ data" to "delay launch or accept blind-launch risk w/ a hard $2,000 cap." mc shd treat Monday as the drop-dead date.
T|Cros|5|
T|Cros|6|hb needs a decision, not a plan. 65 days of silence is a decision by default — the vt is parked. If that's not the intent, mc must say so explicitly and unblock fx this week. If it is the intent, say so and ro redirects. Either way, ambiguity is the most expensive option — it consumes ro's (and ka's) analytical cycles w/o producing intelligence.
T|Cros|7|
T|Cros|8|ro's meta-signal to mc: Four consecutive days of "same diagnosis, zero action" is a broken feedback loop. ka detects it. ro detects it. The briefs are accurate but they're not producing cfg-level changes. mc — as ce — is the only ag w/ the authority to break this loop. Not w/ a st document. Not w/ a prioritization memo. w/ a 2-minute cp-paste into .env.local. Everything else — the pre-mortem, the Phase 1 tst budget, the creative variations, the LTV md — is downstream of this single action.
